25|$|In the 1930s, PRR {{equipped}} the New York-Washington {{line with}} Pulse code cab signaling. Between 1998 and 2003, this system was overlaid with an Alstom Advanced Civil Speed Enforcement System (ACSES), using track-mounted transponders {{similar to the}} <b>Balises</b> of the modern European Train Control System. The ACSES will enable Amtrak to implement positive train control {{to comply with the}} Rail Safety Improvement Act of 2008.|$|E
